</font><P><TABLE background="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/backg.gif"><TR><TD><IMG src="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/elawndarhead.jpg" border=0></TD><TD><P><font color="white">      "You will never become a Knight at this rate"<BR><BR><BR>"Me 'barsh.  Just heal Pally"</font></P></TD><TD><IMG src="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/elaundarhead.jpg" border=0></TD></TR><TR><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Elawndar<BR>Warrior 51</font></P></TD><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Frayed Knot<BR>The Rathe</font></P></TD><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Elaundar Nobillium<BR>Paladin 53</font></P></TD></TR></TABLE><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Wog</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>6</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12:46:25 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Some incorrect information...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The 2 AM rule should not be violated. The guild that has the next day reserved should not have to pay for the mistakes of someone else.<br>
<br>
The one time I have been on a BB call up, we cleared essentially the entire plane in 4 hours, and killed CT before the 2 AM deadline. <br>
<br>
It wasn't an enjoyable experience for anyone there. The guild that we were assisting probably could have taken CT by themselves, they just wanted to make sure there wasn't any fallout from not calling in BB soon enough. They had a bad night, shit happens. Wasn't thier fault.<br>
<br>
The problem I had with it personally, is that we had to essentially take over their raid to get it done. I'm sure they had to have been let down because of that. It would have been much more pleasant if 10-15 higher level, capable people were sprinkled throughout <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  their</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> groups. They would have been able to keep their own assists, use their own tactics (with advice from the BB guild members there) and essentially keep it as <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  their</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> raid. <br>
<br>
That's a perfect world. It aint gonna happen that way, I understand that. Communication problems, lack of familiarity among people, etc. all combine to make this approach hard. I think that's the goal to shoot for. <br>
<br>
Here is an idea...If CT is up and there is any question about the posting guild being able to kill CT before 2 AM, they call for <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  1</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> high level, experienced group of people from the BB guild <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  at the start of the raid.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If it looks like the posting guild can handle it before 2 AM, the group from the BB guild can call it a night. If not, there is already a group from the BB guild there to help ease the transition when it becomes evident that a call up is necessary.<br>
<br>
The BB group that is there will have a good idea of how the quickly the plane is being cleared, and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> know by a reasonable time whether a call up needs to be made. If the posting guild doesn't agree, the BB group can leave the zone and let the posting guild deal with the aftermath. <br>
<br>
This isn't to spoon feed newer guilds with high level &quot;babysitters&quot;. The one BB group there is going to have it in their best interests to make the call as early as possible so they don't waste their time. Once it has been decided if a call up is needed, either the BB guild is called up, or the BB group there can leave.<br>
<br>
There wouldn't be any of the problem with BB guilds getting called up late, because members of the BB guild would be part of the decision making process. If they feel that a call up is needed, and the posting guild refuses to call them up at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> the time the decision is made by the BB group there</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, the posting guild has to live with the consequences. If they clear CT, great. If not, they lose a month of posting privelages.<br>
<br>
If the BB guild <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> called up at the time the BB group requests and fails to kill CT, they go to the back of the rotation, and their status as a BB guild should be re-evaluated. It isn't about whether or not the BB guild can clear fear with CT up in x hours, its about can they mobilize at a moments notice around the clock to handle it. There are a lot of guilds that can down CT, how many can scrape together the people needed quickly any time of the day? If a guild can't do that, it doesn't matter how many uber mobs they can kill, they shouldn't be a BB guild.<br>
<br>
BTW, I'm just a peon with an opinion...<br>
<br>
</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A> at: 2/5/01 12:53:07 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujerricaevilbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrica EvilBringer</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede Slavedriver</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>134</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2:00:19 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/Hollywood/Hills/7069/jerrica2.jpg WIDTH=187 HEIGHT=187></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Some incorrect information...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">&quot;KEG and Bots weren't even close, common difference both had to clear the plane from scratch =(&quot;<br>
